I enjoy the concept of a meme that is affecting animals rather than humans and I haven't seen such an article in a while. I feel like there were couple (or maybe one) grammar mistakes in the article, but they were minor enough and I forgot what they were.

An interesting idea and a solid execution - that why I upvoted.

I must note, that I may have glanced over a paragraph or two (instead of reading them), but that was not enough to lower my enjoyment of the article.







